The paper discusses a privacy-preserving learning algorithm for ELM classification over vertically partitioned data, which involves secure multi-party computation. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the categories of computer security (cs.CR) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper deals with data partitioning and privacy concerns, which could also place it in the categories of databases (cs.DB), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
